condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Loan Agreement, Schedule 2, section I, clause B: Anti-corruption | Description :The Borrower shall ensure thatthe Project is carried out in accordance with the provisions of the Anti-Corruption Guidelines | Frequency :Monthly

Finance Agreement :Project Agreement, Schedule, section I, clause A, bullet 3 | Description :EVN shall maintain, throughout theduration of Project Implementation, a Task Force be responsible for providing facilitation and overall guidance support to theProject Implementing Entities. | Frequency :Monthly

Finance Agreement :Project Agreement, Schedule, section I, clause A, bullet 6 | Description :EVN and TSHPCO shall enter into, by nolater than one year prior to the start up operation of TSHP, a Power Purchase Agreement, forselling and purchasing energy to begenerated by TSHP | Due Date :30-Sep-2016

Finance Agreement :Project Agreement, Schedule, section I, clause B | Description :TSHPCO shall maintain a Project OperationsManual acceptable to the Bank setting forth guidelines, policies, and procedures for theimplementation of the Project | Frequency:Monthly

Finance Agreement :Project Agreement, Schedule, section I, clause C | Description :TSHPCO shall ensure that its Respective Part ofthe Project is carried out in accordance with the provisions of the Governance and Accountability Framework | Frequency :Monthly

Finance Agreement :Project Agreement, Schedule, section I, clause D, bullet 10 | Description :TSHPCO shall maintain, throughout theduration of Project implementation, an independent Project Technical Advisory Panel acceptable to the Bank | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Project Agreement, Schedule, section I, clause D, bullet 4(c) | Description :In the implementation of Part 1 (b)of the Project, TSHPCO shall provide supplemental support to affected Persons who have lost between 10% to 25% of their totalproductive assets | Frequency :Monthly

Finance Agreement :Project Agreement, Schedule, section I, clause D, bullet 9 | Description :TSHPCO shall maintain, throughout theduration of Project implementation or at a date accepted by the Bank, the Environmental and Social Panel of Experts acceptable tothe Bank | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Project Agreement, Schedule, section II, clause B | Description :Except as the Bank may otherwise agree inwriting, NPT shall comply with financial conditions stated in the Schedule, section II, clause B of the Project Agreement |Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Project Agreement, Schedule, section II, clause B | Description :Except as the Bank may otherwise agree inwriting, TSHPCO shall comply with financial conditions stated in the Schedule, section II, clause B of the Project Agreement |Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Project Agreement, Schedule, section II, clause B, bullet 12 | Description :EVN shall promptly provide TSHPCOsufficient counterpart funding for financing the Project on terms and conditions acceptable to the Bank | Frequency :Yearly
